social_posts.post_text: Brand new, and in time to wrap for a child you love for Christmas! If you’ve been to my biblical theology workshop you’ll recognize it’s a kids version of my message about the king. 10ofThose is shipping now! https://us.10ofthose.com/product/9781914966194/the-true-king-hardback
I’m not much of a Christmas decorator, but I’m really happy with the way Etsy helped me turn my Christmas tree into a Christ tree this year!

One of the things I'm looking forward to most in 2023 is getting to interact with women at Biblical Theology Workshops around the country and in several foreign countries. My prayer for every woman who comes is that it will help her to love Christ more and long more for his return. And I find myself praying that prayer for myself as I enter this new year. 
I'd love for you to join me if you're near any of these upcoming cities. Registration opens today at 10 for spring workshops. You can find the complete list of cities and dates at the link on my bio.
Care to guess who was the first on the dance floor tonight at @courtneycdoctor’s daughter’s wedding? #comeoncelebrateandhaveagoodtime
So happy to get to celebrate the upcoming marriage of our son to the lovely Amanda.

Looking for a Christ-centered ministry in Turkey that you can trust? My friends at Servant Group International have been on the ground in Turkey since a similar earthquake in 1999. They have sent four teams of volunteers to the affected areas. This is where I'm sending money and I hope you might consider it too. Go to servantgroup.org and click through on the "Earthquake Relief in Turkey" links.

~Nancy Guthrie, Praying through the Bible for your Kids

I'm looking forward to doing a Biblical Theology Workshop for Women in Cali, Colombia in August. The host, Faith Church, has already registered 300 women. They have space for 50 more, but need additional funds to be able to add more women. The cost per person is $30. If you'd like to pay for 1 or 2 or 10 women to attend the workshop, tax deductible donations can be made to ConexusLA and mailed to: ConexusLA, 209 W Palmer Dr., New Bern, NC 28560. Thanks for considering helping to make it possible for more women to get this training! http://transformadacolombia.org/

I'm looking forward to this RTS online discussion next Tuesday with @ligonduncan and @bgladd! Bunches of books being given away. Registration is free, but required. https://rts.regfox.com/rtsj-odf-feb-2023-bib-theo
Thanks for the help, girls.
My parents. This is love.
The fine people of @apostlesatl know just what I like and are ready for 800 women at a workshop tomorrow.
What a privilege to tell the story of the Lamb at the company-wide chapel at Ramsey Solutions this morning. Worthy is the Lamb who was slain to receive glory and honor!

The last week has been incredibly sad in Nashville. And we know the sadness is only beginning to settle in and the trauma will take a lot of time to heal. We’re all so connected to each other, especially among the numerous PCA churches. In the midst of the sad, it was meaningful to be with so many brothers and sisters we’ve known for so many years to honor Christ for his work in and through Katherine Koonce and to just love each other.

We've had some last-minute cancellations for Bible at the Beach and really need to fill up our rooms at the beautiful Lodge at Gulf Shores. So if you'd like a discounted room ($224/$254) at The Lodge, and a great time around God's word with good friends, please grab a spot by 3 p.m. tomorrow!

Those of you who were there know exactly what I mean when I say that I have no words for how much fun we had at Bible at the Beach 2023. Life is too short to miss out on doing ministry with best friends.

The secret to my productivity and sanity: my two Amys. Amy Kruis, Director of Author Relations and Acquisitions Editor at Crossway, and Amy Kannel, who manages the Biblical Theology Workshops and helps me with Personal Bible Studies and Leader's Guides to go with my studies. They're both brilliant and capable and indispensable. Everyone needs Amys like this in her life.

I’m so excited for the four workshops I have around the country over the next four weekends in: Tampa • Phoenix • Bluffton • Los Angeles. It’s not too late to join me!

And I’m excited to announce that registration is now open for workshops this summer and fall in: Colombia, Scotland, England, and Italy!

Link in bio.

Twenty-one years ago @tyndalehouse hired me to work with the media who were all chasing after Gracia Burnham for an interview after she spent a year as a hostage of the Abu Sayyaf in the jungles of the Philippines. She was grieving the death of her husband, Martin, who was killed in the rescue and adjusting to life back in the states. It was a privilege to work with her then and a joy to see her tonight at my Biblical Theology Workshop in Tampa.
Happy to be with my family today in Houston.

SUMMER BIBLE STUDY!
If you live in the Nashville/Franklin area, or if you'll be passing through this summer, I'd love to invite you to come to the summer Bible study I lead at my church, Cornerstone Presbyterian Church in downtown Franklin. 
We're going to work our way through the first nine chapters of the book of Acts on Tuesday nights in June and July at 6:30. 
June 6: You Will Be my Witnesses (1:1—26)
June 13: I Will Pour Out My Spirit (2:1-47)
June 20: In Jesus the Resurrection from the Dead (3:1- 4:31)
June 27: You Will Not Be Able to Overthrow Them (4:32-5:42)
(no study July 4)
July 11: And the Word of God Continued to Increase (6:1- 7:60)
July 18: They Were All Scattered (8:2-40)
July 25: God's Chosen Instrument (9:1-31)
You'll soon find Personal Bible Study questions to help you prepare for each session available for download on the women's ministry page of the Cornerstone website. And our youth will be selling Acts Scripture Journals the first couple of weeks at the study. I look forward to opening up this important book about our family history with you this summer. I hope to see you there!

It's been a year and a half since my friends Shamsia and Ramazan escaped Afghanistan and settled in Louisville. They have started a Farsi-speaking fellowship there and are seeking to minister to the many Afghans who have settled there. One of the biggest challenges for newcomers is transportation. So they're started a GoFundMe account to raise some money to purchase two cars and two minivans for four families in their church just getting started in the states. If you'd like to help, go to: https://gofund.me/c6bec208. Link in bio.
What a fun night with these amazing people, Julius & JiHee Kim.  #sidehurtsfromlaughing

Twelve years ago today I began filming the Seeing Jesus in the Old Testament video series. I am beyond grateful for the way seeing Christ in all the scriptures has changed my life and how God has used this series in the lives of so many, giving them some of the same "I never saw that before" experiences that I had.
Summer Sunday morning hearing a fabulous message about speaking the truth from @nateshurden and worshipping with two of my favorite people @rhdillard and Gwen Smith. #lifeinchristisgood
I was digging in some boxes today and found the original of a poem David wrote to me that I quoted in Even Better Than Eden. Evidently I missed a verse. For your reading pleasure . . . #hearttouching
Driving home from Bible study and so very grateful for the beauty of God’s word and God’s world.

There’s something to be said for having the right equipment. We’ve had this fallen tree from the lot next door in our yard for 18 months waiting for them to remove it when clearing the lot to start building a house. Glad to see it go. Not looking forward to the drilling and hammering and long days of construction noise to come. I’ll try not to complain too much.
Rainy Saturday morning backyard bliss.

David figured out last week that we will be on six continents over the next ten months doing Biblical Theology Workshops and other speaking events. Would love to see you along the way. Link in bio to all of the currently available info.
The beautiful sound of 550 women in Bogotá searching the scriptures to find the Bible’s story of blessing and  curse.

My sweet husband honored his mom beautifully today at a memorial service for her. I’m deeply grateful to his mom for her part in shaping the man who loves me so well. And I’m enormously grateful to David’s sister, Janet, for carrying the load of her parents’ care for so many years.
What fun to offer a Biblical Theology workshop on a sunny day in Inverness. Only in Scotland do 100 out of 400 registrants have last names that begin with Mac.

I’m in Munich Germany tonight and feeling that many of my friends are here with me!
My dad fought the good fight. He finished the race. He kept the faith. Away from the body; at home with the Lord.
If you knew my dad, then you know this captures him perfectly. Bye, dad. Thanks for this photo, @bethiphr.
Pretty much all I want for Christmas.

I'm so happy that so many of my older as well as new books are becoming available in Spanish! Hearing Jesus Speak Into Your Sorrow is a book so close to my heart now available in Spanish! Next year @tyndaleespanol will publish Praying Through The Bible for Your Kids in Spanish!

David and I are so grateful that two couples who attended our Respite Retreat for couples who have lost children are now offering retreats and seeing couples experience joy and hope again. Our partners, Gabe and Monica deGarmeaux have room for 5 or 6 more couples at their next retreat in January. If you or someone you know has lost a child, I hope you’ll check out this healing weekend retreat near New Braunfels, Texas. Go to respiteretreatattheriver.com.

Here’s something for your Christmas list. Or you could just go ahead and register and tell them later that it’s your Christmas gift from them: a few days at the beach in Gulf Shores, Alabama studying the book of Acts. Only 30 spots left, so register soon if you’d like to join us in April! Link in bio.

🚪 Nancy Guthrie (@nancyguthrienashville) ist Bibellehrerin in ihrer Heimatgemeinde, der Cornerstone Presbyterian Church in Franklin (USA 🇺🇸), sowie weltweit auf verschiedenen Konferenzen. Sie hat zahlreiche Bücher und Podcasts veröffentlicht. Sie und ihr Mann haben eine Organisation gegründet, um Erholung für Ehepaare anzubieten, die den Tod eines Kindes erlebt haben. Vor einigen Wochen erschien ihr Buch 📕 „Besser als Eden“ bei Verbum Medien (@verbummedien).
